          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript to be used for private or public consultation, recitation, and prayer; likely taken from a larger compendium compiled from a purāṇic source dealing with festivals, observances (vratas), pūjās (rites of worshiping deities), and mythic origins of these rites. Dedicated to Budha (Mercury), considered the son of the Moon, describing various rites to be performed in honor of this deity (such as bathing, fasting, offerings of milk, and others).</summary>
